<s> From http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/struct/lists.html : "Another application of DL, for example, is for marking up dialogues, with each DT naming a speaker, and each DD containing his or her words."  </s>
<s> That clearly isn't a matter of terms and descriptions, so I think it justifies the use of dl for general name/value pairs.  </s>
<s> I'm now happy again that this isn't HTML abuse, and indeed is quite appropriate.  </s>
